    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at MRL 2. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded with concrete flow-rate (1.0–7.0 L/min), rotational speed (1500–3500 RPM), pressure (0–120 mmHg), and geometry tolerance (tip clearance 0.15–0.45 mm) bounds. Validation activities cover five operating points spanning the central envelope with honest documentation of increased uncertainty at envelope extremes. Discretization error exceeds requirements (GCI 3.1% vs. 5% budget). Six factors are appropriately scoped out with documented rationale consistent with MRL 2 expectations for a Class II device. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is met at all nominal operating points with quantified uncertainty. The credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the regulatory decision that the CFD model can reliably identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions within the declared envelope.",
